\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Proof
\emph default
.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\I(X)$
\end_inset

 is the set of all polynomials that vanish on the given points.
 Clearly, 
\begin_inset Formula $\prod_{j=1}^{r}(x-a_{j})$
\end_inset

 is one such polynomial.
 We need to show that any other such polynomial belongs to the ideal generated
 by 
\begin_inset Formula $\prod_{j=1}^{r}(x-a_{j})$
\end_inset

.
 We know that each of the 
\begin_inset Formula $(x-a_{j})$
\end_inset

 are irreducible.
