\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in\I(X),$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $p(x)$
\end_inset

 vanishes on 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
 Iteratively applying the factor theorem (Corollary 0.48), we have 
\begin_inset Formula $p(x)=q(x)\prod_{j=1}^{r}(x-a_{j})$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $q(x)\in K[x]$
\end_inset

.
