\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is a multiple (in the polynomial ring) of 
\begin_inset Formula $\prod_{j=1}^{r}(x-a_{j})$
\end_inset

 means 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is in the ideal generated by 
\begin_inset Formula $\prod_{j=1}^{r}(x-a_{j})$
\end_inset

.
